12/01/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish Prime Minister Abdullah Gul on Saturday (11 January) called on Iraqi leader Saddam Hussein to avert war and warned that a conflict could threaten stability in the entire region. 
"UN decisions must be implemented in a way that leaves no room for any doubt," he said before departing for Saudi Arabia, where he met with Crown Prince Abdullah. 
In separate news, Turkey allowed US inspection teams to visit air force and naval bases on Friday as part of preparations for a possible campaign against Baghdad. 
(Anadolu Agency, Okaz, TRT, Turkish Daily News, AP, Reuters, AFP - 11/01/03; INA, Anadolu Agency - 10/01/03)
